FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE, CAPRINE - ISRAEL (02): OIE
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 2 Jan 2007
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Alert [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/reports/en_imm_0000004351_20070102_185949.pdf>

Foot and mouth disease, Israel
---------------------------------
Information received on 2 Jan 2007 from Dr. Moshe Chaimovitz, Director,
Veterinary Services and Animal Health, Ministry of Agriculture and Rural
Development, Beit Dagan, Israel.
Summary:
Report type: Immediate notification
Start date: 28 Dec 2006
Date of confirmation of event: 1 Jan 2007
Report date: 2 Jan 2007
Date submitted to OIE: 2 Jan 2007
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: December 2005
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: FMD virus O
Nature of diagnosis: Suspicion, Clinical, Laboratory (basic), Laboratory
(advanced), Necropsy
Report pertains to entire country
New Outbreaks:
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak Location: Hazafon (Netu'a, Acco)
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/reports/en_imm_0000004351_20070102_185949.pdf>
Total animals affected:
Species Goats
Susceptible: 520
Cases: 260
Deaths: 90
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0
Outbreak statistics:
Species: Goats
Apparent morbidity rate: 50.00 percent
Apparent mortality rate: 17.31 percent
Apparent case fatality rate: 34.62 percent
Proportion susceptible removed:* 17.31 percent
*Removed from the susceptible population either through death, destruction
or slaughter
Epidemiology: Source of infection is unknown or inconclusive
Control measures: Measures already applied included movement control inside
the country; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s); quarantine;
vaccination permitted, no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: Screening
Laboratory name and type: National FMD Laboratory, Kimron Vet. Inst.
(National laboratory)
Tests and results:
Species - Goats
Test - antigen (Ag) detection ELISA
Test date - 1 Jan 2007
Result - Positive
Species - Goats
Test - pathogen isolation on cell culture
Test date - 1 Jan 2007
Result - Positive
